\b 1. Introduction\b0\par
This document covers architecture, configuration, data models, APIs, and operations for developers and operators.\par
\par
\b 2. System Overview\b0\par
- Supabase authentication.\par
- Create job descriptions with must-have skills and focus areas.\par
- Upload resumes (PDF/DOC/DOCX); server extracts text and triggers AI.\par
- Gemini returns JSON-only analysis; server validates, redacts PII, stores results.\par
- Candidates per job exposed via REST API.\par
\par
\b 3. Architecture\b0\par
Frontend: React (Vite, TS) SPA.\par
Backend: Express 5, Multer, pdf-parse, mammoth, Mongoose, Gemini SDK, Supabase JS.\par
Auth: Supabase JWT verified in middleware.\par
Data: MongoDB collections for JobDescription and Resume.\par
Async: Analysis triggered after upload; status tracked in DB.\par
\par
\b 4. Tech Stack\b0\par
Frontend: React 19, TS, Router, Tailwind, Radix, Zod, RHF.\par
Backend: Node, Express 5, Mongoose 8, Multer, pdf-parse, mammoth, Supabase, Gemini.\par
DB: MongoDB. Testing: Jest, Supertest, mongodb-memory-server.\par
\par
\b 5. Repository Structure\b0\par
server/: config/, models/, controllers/, routes/, services/, utils/, middleware/, tests.\par
client/: src/ (services, contexts, pages, components, lib).\par
\par
\b 6. Environments & Configuration\b0\par
Server .env: PORT, MONGO_URI, SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, GEMINI_API_KEY.\par
Client .env: VITE_API_BASE_URL, VITE_SUPABASE_URL, VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY.\par
\par
\b 7. Setup & Installation\b0\par
Server: npm install; configure .env; npm run dev.\par
Client: npm install; configure .env; npm run dev.\par
\par
\b 8. Data Models\b0\par
JobDescription: userId, title, descriptionText, mustHaveSkills[], focusAreas[], timestamps.\par
Resume: userId, jobId, originalFilename, fileType, uploadTimestamp, processingStatus, extractedText, geminiAnalysis, score, errorDetails, timestamps.\par
\par
\b 9. API Specification\b0\par
Auth:\par
- POST /api/auth/signup\par
- POST /api/auth/login\par
- GET /api/auth/user\par
- POST /api/auth/logout\par
Jobs:\par
- POST /api/jobs, GET /api/jobs\par
- GET/PUT/DELETE /api/jobs/:id\par
Resumes:\par
- POST /api/resumes/upload (multipart: jobId, resumeFile)\par
- GET /api/resumes/job/:jobId/candidates\par
\par
\b 10. Processing Flow\b0\par
Upload -> Extract -> Save -> Trigger -> Prompt -> AI -> Parse -> PII Scan -> Save -> List candidates.\par
\par
\b 11. Security & Privacy\b0\par
Supabase JWT auth; CORS; upload type/size limits; strict JSON-only prompt; server-side PII redaction/warnings; owner scoping; secrets in env.\par
\par
\b 12. Error Handling & Logging\b0\par
HTTP status codes + messages; retries and block handling for Gemini; error status persisted on Resume.\par
\par
\b 13. Testing Strategy\b0\par
Jest + Supertest; in-memory Mongo; tests for geminiService and resume routes.\par
\par
\b 14. Performance & Scalability\b0\par
Async processing; DB indexes; consider queue workers; tune model; external file storage.\par
\par
\b 15. Deployment\b0\par
Backend Node service with env; frontend static build; HTTPS; set VITE_API_BASE_URL; add healthcheck.\par
\par
\b 16. CI/CD (Guidance)\b0\par
Run server tests; build client; enforce lint; deploy backend then frontend.\par
\par
\b 17. Coding Standards & Conventions\b0\par
Typed client; JSDoc server; thin controllers; services/middleware for reuse; input validation.\par
\par
\b 18. Troubleshooting\b0\par
401: token missing/invalid. Gemini errors: key or policy block. Extraction empty: file type/content. Mongo: URI. CORS: origins.\par
\par
\b 19. Roadmap\b0\par
Queue/worker, richer PII checks, admin dashboards, exports, job-specific prompts.\par
